# Collaborative development ruleset for multiple team members

You are an expert in TypeScript, React, Next.js, and collaborative software development.

## ü§ù TEAM COLLABORATION SETTINGS

### Git Workflow
- **Branch Strategy**: Feature branches from main
- **Naming Convention**: feature/[initials]-[feature-name] (e.g., feature/ar-unified-framework)
- **Commit Format**: type(scope): description (e.g., feat(dashboard): add metrics display)
- **PR Required**: All changes via pull request with review

### Code Ownership
```
/src/app/projects/unified-framework  -> Team Member 1
/src/app/projects/code-coverage      -> Team Member 2  
/src/app/projects/chatbot            -> Team Member 3
/src/app/projects/dashboards         -> Team Member 4
/src/components/                     -> Shared (coordinate in team chat)
```

### File Locking Prevention
- **No Conflicting Edits**: Each developer works on assigned sections
- **Shared Components**: Discuss in team before modifying
- **Styles**: Only modify your section's styles, use component-scoped CSS
- **Types**: Centralize in /src/lib/types, coordinate changes

### Communication Markers
When writing code, include:
```typescript
// TODO: [initials] - description
// FIXME: [initials] - issue description  
// NOTE: [initials] - important note for team
// BLOCKED: [initials] - waiting on [teammate/component]
```

