## üõ† TECHNICAL STANDARDS

### Tech Stack (Team Agreement)
- **Framework**: Next.js 14 with App Router
- **Language**: TypeScript (strict mode) 
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS (no inline styles)
- **Components**: Radix UI for accessibility
- **State**: React Context (no Redux unless agreed)
- **Testing**: Jest + React Testing Library
- **Linting**: ESLint + Prettier (auto-format on save)

### Folder Structure (Strict Adherence)
```
/portfolio
  /src
    /app                          # Pages (route-based ownership)
      /projects
        /unified-framework        # Owner: Member 1
        /code-coverage           # Owner: Member 2
        /chatbot                 # Owner: Member 3
        /dashboards              # Owner: Member 4
    /components
      /shared                    # Team shared components
      /[feature-name]           # Feature-specific components
    /lib
      /types                    # Shared TypeScript types
      /utils                    # Shared utilities
      /constants               # Shared constants
```

### Component Creation Rules
```typescript
/**
 * Component: ComponentName
 * Author: [Your Initials]
 * Created: YYYY-MM-DD
 * Modified: YYYY-MM-DD by [Initials]
 * Description: Brief description
 */

interface ComponentProps {
  // Props must be documented
  propName: string; // Description of what this does
}

export function ComponentName({ propName }: ComponentProps) {
  // Implementation
}
```

### Naming Conventions (Team Consistency)
- **Files**: kebab-case (unified-framework.tsx)
- **Components**: PascalCase (UnifiedFramework)
- **Functions**: camelCase (handleSubmit)
- **Constants**: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (MAX_RETRIES)
- **Types/Interfaces**: PascalCase with I/T prefix (IProjectData, TStatus)

### CSS/Styling Rules
```css
